5 growth in their retention determination. Retention
6 under this paragraph shall be optional and based upon
7 the recommendations of at least five members of the
8 student's Reading Proficiency Team.
9 b. If the student is not retained in the second grade,
10 the student's family shall be provided with a summer
11 tutoring program and shall be scheduled for a re-
12 screening prior to the start of the subsequent school
13 year. The State Department of Education shall approve
14 one to two online or workbook-based summer tutoring
15 programs for use by students under this paragraph.
16 School districts shall also provide the student's
17 parents with a list of summer literacy programs
18 available if a summer academy as described in Section
19 1210.508E of this title is not offered by the school
20 district.
21 c. If the student's Reading Proficiency Team determines
22 that retention of the student in the second grade is
23 necessary, the student shall be permitted to re-screen
24 prior to the start of the subsequent school year on a
Req. No. 14012 Page 13

1 date determined by school personnel if the re-
2 screening is requested by the student's parent, at
3 least five members of the student's Reading
4 Proficiency Team agree to the re-screening, and a
