9 3. a. If a third grade student has not met a proficient
10 benchmark, as defined by the State Department of
11 Education in accordance with paragraph 5 of subsection
12 D of this section, by the end-of-year screening, the
13 student's Reading Proficiency Team shall meet prior to
14 the end of the school year to discuss retention of the
15 student. Retention under this paragraph shall be
16 mandatory unless at least five members of the
17 student's Reading Proficiency Team recommend the
18 student move to fourth grade and one of the following
19 exceptions are met:
20 (1) the student has an Individual Education Plan or a
21 Section 504 plan,
22 (2) the student has a medical exemption such as a
23 severe illness or family emergency that did not
24
Req. No. 14012 Page 14

1 allow for adequate screening or classwork
2 completion, or
3 (3) the student was previously retained and has shown
4 an eighty percent (80%) improvement in grade
5 level work over their third grade year.
6 b. If the student is not retained in the third grade, the
7 student's family shall be provided with a summer
8 tutoring program and shall be scheduled for a re-
9 screening prior to the start of the subsequent school
10 year. The State Department of Education shall approve
11 one to two online or workbook-based summer tutoring
12 programs for use by students under this paragraph.
13 School districts shall also provide the student's
14 parents with a list of summer literacy programs
15 available if a summer academy as described in Section
16 1210.508E of this title is not offered by the school
17 district.
18 H. Each school district shall annually report in an electronic
19 format to the State Department of Education, the Office of
20 Educational Quality and Accountability, and the Secretary of
21 Education the number of students in kindergarten through third grade
22 per grade level who exhibit grade-level reading proficiency, the
23 number of students per grade level who received intensive
24 intervention services pursuant to paragraph 2 of subsection F of
Req. No. 14012 Page 15

1 this section, the number of students per grade level who attended a
2 summer academy as provided for in Section 1210.508E of this title,
3 the number of students per grade level who exhibited improved
4 reading proficiency after completion of intensive intervention
5 services, and the number of students per grade level who are still
